	(text_box "PROG3 Termination Charge Current\n\nStandard practice for Li-Ion batteries is to terminate charging when current drops to 5-10% of the fast charge current (0.05C to 0.1C).\n\nFor 2000mAh battery with 1000mA fast charge:\n10% termination = 100mA → R(PROG3) = 1000V / 100mA = 10kΩ\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 83.82 175.895 0)
		(size 59.69 21.59)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type color)
			(color 0 0 255 0.06)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "25849068-c931-40a4-adff-3ad8ca3083ca")
	)
	(text_box "PROG1 Charging Current\n\nUsing the formula: I(REG) = 1000V / R(PROG1)\n\nFor 2000mah battery with 0.25C * 2000mah = 0.5A charge rate. 1000V / 0.5A = 2kΩ"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 44.45 175.895 0)
		(size 36.83 21.59)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
